					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It doesn't matter. None of this code is good.<br /><br />Look on the bright side. If your file weren't corrupt, it would correctly find it's way to the start of your code (reset), at which point, lots of bad things happen that don't make sense, and wouldn't do what you want. At some point, an NMI would fire, and it would go to NMI, and never come back (without an RTI).<br /><br />Removed comment. Sounded too harsh.<br /><br />Would it be ok if I rewrote your code, with code that actually works? Or would you rather work it out for yourself?</div>

					
